#100DaysOfCode – Day 11
Today, I learned about the `pass` statement in Python and its role as a placeholder in programs. I explored how it can be used in functions, loops, conditional statements, and classes when the implementation is yet to be added. This helped me understand how to write structured code while developing programs step by step.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 12
Today, I learned about local and global variables in Python and how variable scope affects accessibility within a program. I practiced using local variables inside functions and global variables across different parts of a program, gaining a better understanding of scope management and code organization.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 13
Today, I learned about recursion in Python and explored its different types. I understood how recursive functions call themselves to solve problems by breaking them into smaller subproblems. I also practiced recursive examples to strengthen my understanding of recursive thinking and problem-solving.

#100DaysOfCode – Day 14
Today, I learned about arguments in Python and their different types. I explored how arguments are passed to functions, including positional, keyword, default, and variable-length arguments. Practicing these concepts helped me understand how to write more flexible, reusable, and efficient functions.
